Asli Telli:
 
“The Cambalache collective in Mexico city, comprised of feminist ecologists, intersects both digital and physical commons and has a say in material commons. They do not only live physically within the principles they have diligently set for themselves as autonomous commons collective, but they also belong to DAOs ecosystem for their accounting and also carry out bottom-up campaigns to keep their space as well as their second-hand shop, botanic garden as well as their quasi-academic digital archive on feminist ecological movement.”
 
(email, July 2022)

